In the Cretaceous period, huge terrobodies, carnivorous dinosaurs, were walking on the Earth, walking on two legs.
Although the king of all dinosaurs - Tyrannosaurus rex - lived for several million years after Borealopelta, this armored dinosaur could have been a favorite prey to his equally gruesome ancestors.
